    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Valveless brass aerophones with conical bores. These were used mostly in the military to give signals to the infantry. Now chiefly used to refer to trumpet-like instruments of this kind in the Middle Ages and Renaissance, distinguished from modern "bugles."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
